------------------------------------------------------------------------
r2959 | andlov | 2017-04-26 12:37:42 +0200 (Wed, 26 Apr 2017) | 1 line

Use mutex lock on table name (as resource name) to prevent concurrent update table index (in delete() and save()) leaving result set keys not present in any table index. This is rarely happening, but inspection shows that under certain circumstances we get dangling result set keys that are not invalidated. The observered use case seems to be during correction.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
